==English==
===Etymology===
[[de-]] + [[shopper]]

===Noun===
'''deshopper''' (''plural'' '''deshoppers''')

#A person who buys an item, uses it once and then returns it to the place it was bought for a [[refund]], having intended to do this when buying the item.

====Quotations====
*'''2004''' - British retailers should be on the look out for suspect deshoppers over the Christmas period, warns Brunel University. Few retailers have adequate return policies that prohibit customers from buying goods with no intention of keeping them. &mdash; [http://www.brunel.ac.uk/news/press/releases/1204/deshopping.shtml Brunel University's website]

